Instruction:
1-Copy the file HaltRebootDaemon.sh in /etc/init.d
2-Copy the dir HaltRebootDaemon in /usr/local/bin
3-Set the chmod of all the file to 744
4-Launch the command "sudo rc-update.d HaltRebootDaemon.sh defaults"
5-Reboot

The command "sudo /etc/init.d/HaltRebootDaemon.sh status" give the status of the daemon
Other Parameter of the command are start|stop|restart

Input/Output necessary for the python script:
-Push button that close to Ground (Input in Pull-up) connected to GPIO28 
-Green LED (active with +3.3V from the output) connected to GPIO29
-Red LED (active with +3.3V from the output) connected to GPIO29

